      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The need</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">Taqueria la Güera had the food, the team, and the location. What was missing was visual presence — an identity that made their truck stand out from a distance and made their storefront look professional and appetizing.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">When a food business is out on the road or parked at a corner, the banner is the first point of contact with the customer. If it does not communicate clearly, the customer drives past. If it does, it is free advertising all day long.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">What we did</h2>
      <ul class="checklist mb-8">
        <li><strong><a href="/en/services/branding-logo-design-treasure-coast/" style="color:var(--primary)">Logo design</a></strong> — a visual identity for the taqueria that works on banners, menus, social media, and any future materials.</li>
        <li><strong>Truck vinyl banner</strong> — design featuring the logo, main dishes, and prices. Visible, eye-catching, and easy to read from the street or parking lot.</li>
        <li><strong>Storefront banner</strong> — the same visual system applied to the physical location. Consistent look between the truck and the point of sale.</li>
        <li><strong>Dish photography integration</strong> — real images of their tacos and dishes on the banners to trigger appetite at first glance.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The result</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">A taqueria that used to blend into the background now has a visual presence that competes with much larger businesses. The truck became a mobile advertisement: wherever the vehicle goes, the brand goes too.</p>

